  "body": "The layout of the input data to the `BN_MUL` zk-SNARK precompile is incorrect. Currently, it looks like this:\r\n\r\n![screenshot620](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3964494/57608112-4d906980-7564-11e9-8a62-87c66712e7c8.png)\r\n\r\nwhich means that the first 32 bytes of the input memory range are occupied by the scalar `n`, and the next 64 bytes are occupied by the curve point. In fact, according the Ethereum test suite and to other implementations like `aleth`, `parity`, and KEVM, the first 64 bytes are the curve point and the next 32 are the scalar, so it should look like this:\r\n\r\n![screenshot621](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3964494/57608931-d3f97b00-7565-11e9-8f15-4f45f9968ee4.png)\r\n\r\n*correct implementation references:*\r\n- [aleth](https://github.com/ethereum/aleth/blob/32f9c88f65fc30d7b682de651e2d40d8b7e26078/libdevcrypto/LibSnark.cpp#L192)\r\n- [parity](https://github.com/paritytech/parity-ethereum/blob/2cf0d7d7757829a8d6d3a65547c96258c73b9b91/ethcore/src/builtin.rs#L467)\r\n- [KEVM](https://github.com/kframework/evm-semantics/blob/master/evm.md#precompiled-contracts)\r\n```\r\n    syntax PrecompiledOp ::= \"ECMUL\"\r\n // --------------------------------\r\n    rule <k> ECMUL => #ecmul((#asWord(DATA [ 0 .. 32 ]), #asWord(DATA [ 32 .. 32 ])), #asWord(DATA [ 64 .. 32 ])) ... </k>\r\n         <callData> DATA </callData>\r\n```",
